{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I have done my best to try to dispel the idea that it never happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And not only me, but there were thousands of American soldiers, British soldiers, Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Dachau was one of hundreds of concentration camps that the Germans maintained.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So there were thousands of British, American, and Russian soldiers who liberated those camps who saw firsthand and thousands and thousands of pictures were taken.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "To say that it never happened is the height of stupidity and viciousness.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I'll fight those type of people till my last breath.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I have great sympathy for the Jewish people who I have no question that something like six million died in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But there are also, in addition to the Jewish people, there were others who died, as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The inmates at Dachau when we arrived, actually, the bulk of them were Russians, Russian civilians.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the next biggest group was Polish and the next biggest group was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We took an almond joy of the number of people by races and we have that-- I have not inventory.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Almost 32,000.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were 25 or 30 different races represented.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some Italians, there were French, Lithuanians-- you name it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some Americans, but they were naturalized Americans who so apparently were caught back when they went back to visit their home areas.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think there were five or six that were naturalized Americans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I never talked-- I talked with one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was-- he was actually an American soldier who had-- was a member of the OSS, which at that time was our equivalent of a-- agency, the spy agency, the CIA.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had been dropped into Germany of some kind of mission and been captured.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
